<p><strong>Schofield and Sims Mental Arithmetic Book 4: Answers (PDF)</strong></p>
<p>The Schofield and Sims Mental Arithmetic series is a popular resource for developing mental math skills in students. Book 4 is designed for students in Year 4 of primary school (ages 8-9) and covers topics such as multiplication, division, fractions, and decimals.</p>
<p>To help students practice and improve their mental arithmetic skills, we have compiled a PDF document containing the answers to all the questions in Book 4. This resource can be downloaded and used for self-study or in conjunction with the textbook.</p>
<p><strong>Questions and Answers</strong></p>
<p><strong>Section 1: Multiplication and Division</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>What is 12 x 7? Answer: 84</li>
<li>Divide 48 by 6. Answer: 8</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Section 2: Fractions and Decimals</strong></p>
<ol start="3">
<li>Find the fraction of 15. Answer: 5/15</li>
<li>Convert 0.75 to a fraction. Answer: 3/4</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Section 3: Addition and Subtraction</strong></p>
<ol start="5">
<li>What is 230 + 450? Answer: 680</li>
<li>Subtract 158 from 320. Answer: 162</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Section 4: Money and Measurement</strong></p>
<ol start="7">
<li>How much is 3 pounds and 15 pence? Answer: Â£3.15</li>
<li>Convert 2 meters to centimeters. Answer: 200 cm</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>Section 5: Problem Solving</strong></p>
<ol start="9">
<li>A farmer has 12 rows of strawberries. Each row has 25 plants. How many strawberry plants does he have in total? Answer: 300</li>
<li>A cyclist travels 15 miles in 3 hours. What is his average speed? Answer: 5 mph</li>
</ol>